HEADWORD: Teratoma
<hw>Ter`a*to"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/,
<?/, monster + <ets>-oma</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A tumor,
sometimes found in newborn children, which is made up of a heterogeneous
mixture of tissues, as of bone, cartilage and muscle.</def>⟦br⟧
